  "response": "Here are steps for an Indian mechanical engineer to apply for a Japanese company:\n\n1. Language Preparation\n- Learn Japanese (JLPT certification preferred)\n- Basic to N3/N2 level recommended\n- Take online/offline Japanese language courses\n\n2. Qualifications\n- Bachelor's/Master's degree in Mechanical Engineering\n- Strong technical skills\n- Work experience preferred\n- Valid passport\n\n3. Job Search Platforms\n- Japan Job Websites\n- LinkedIn\n- Indeed Japan\n- Daijob.com\n- GaijinPot\n- Japan-specific recruitment agencies\n\n4. Visa Requirements\n- Obtain work visa (Engineer/Specialist in Humanities/International Services)\n- Sponsorship from Japanese company\n- Minimum bachelor's degree\n- Relevant work experience\n- Passing skill/technical interviews\n\n5. Application Process\n- Prepare Japanese/English resume\n- Translation of educational documents\n- Professional certifications\n- Portfolio/project details\n- Cover letter\n- Interview preparation\n\n6. Additional Opportunities\n- Engineering recruitment agencies\n- Company direct applications\n- Engineering job fairs\n- Exchange programs\n- Technical conferences/seminars\n\n7. Skill Enhancement\n- CAD software knowledge\n- Advanced technical skills\n- Industry certifications\n- Understanding Japanese work culture\n\nRecommended preparation: 1-2 years of consistent effort.",
